Building & Usage
Local build (MinGW-w64):
Bashg++ -shared -o winmm.dll winmm_proxy.cpp winmm.def -lwinmm -Wl,--subsystem,windows -s -Os
GitHub Actions: Push to main → workflow compiles and uploads artifact automatically.
Installation (simple mode):

Compile/download winmm.dll
Copy onlywinmm.dll to game folder
Run game executable

No extra files needed if using system winmm.dll loading.
Historical Context
The gameport (DA-15 connector) was standard for joysticks in the 90s and almost always integrated into sound cards (Sound Blaster, ESS, Aztech, Media Vision). It shared IRQ/DMA/I/O with audio and MIDI, which is why INF files configure them together.
DirectX 2 (1995) and WinMM APIs were showcased in titles like Doom 95 — hence their strict validation.
